      "text": "Everything in Smalltalk is an object, and all computation is performed by sending\nmessages to objects. Each object is an instance of a class. All instances of a class share the same methods and structure. Every class is a subclass of either another class or \"nil\" (a special object denoting \"no value\"). Each class \"inherits\" the methods and structure of its superclass. So, the key piece of Smalltalk syntax is the message. ",
      "id": "ccfc94d4be7a768313fabd02029ba9ba"
